annotationA: Cdc25-like protein phosphatase twine; Required during meiosis. Regulates the transition from the extended G2 phase to the onset of the first meiotic division; Belongs to the MPI phosphatase family
annotationB: G1/S-specific cyclin-E; Essential for the control of the cell cycle at the G1/S (start) transition. Targeted by archipelago for degradation by the SFC ubiquitin ligase complex
